</span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval\">AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a>   <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">ε</span> &gt; <span class=\"fn\">0</span>,\n    <span class=\"fn\">∃ <span class=\"fn\">δ</span> &gt; <span class=\"fn\">0</span>,\n      <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">E</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.disjWithin\">AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.disjWithin</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span>,\n        <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">∑ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Range.html#Finset.range\">Finset.range</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.1</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.1</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.2</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">δ</span> →\n          <span class=\"fn\">∑ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Range.html#Finset.range\">Finset.range</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.1</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.1</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.2</span>)</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">ε</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The traditional `ε`-`δ` definition of absolutely continuous: A function `f` is\n*absolutely continuous* on `uIcc a b` if for any `ε > 0`, there is `δ > 0` such that for\nany finite disjoint collection of intervals `uIoc (a i) (b i)` for `i < n` where `a i`, `b i` are\nall in `uIcc a b` for `i < n`, if `∑ i ∈ range n, dist (a i) (b i) < δ`, then\n`∑ i ∈ range n, dist (f (a i)) (f (b i)) < ε`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#absolutelyContinuousOnInterval_iff","kind":"theorem","line":158,"name":"absolutelyContinuousOnInterval_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.lean#L158-L170"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval\"><span class=\"name\">AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#PseudoMetricSpace\">PseudoMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval f a b`: A function `f` is *absolutely continuous* on `uIcc a b`\nif the function which (intuitively) maps `uIoc (a i) (b i)`, `i < n` to\n`∑ i ∈ Finset.range n, dist (f (a i)) (f (b i))` tendsto `𝓝 0` wrt `totalLengthFilter` restricted\nto `disjWithin a b`. This is equivalent to the traditional `ε`-`δ` definition: for any `ε > 0`,\nthere is `δ > 0` such that for any finite disjoint collection of intervals `uIoc (a i) (b i)` for\n`i < n` where `a i`, `b i` are all in `uIcc a b` for `i < n`, if\n`∑ i ∈ range n, dist (a i) (b i) < δ`, then `∑ i ∈ range n, dist (f (a i)) (f (b i)) < ε`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval","kind":"def","line":147,"name":"AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.lean#L147-L156"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.tendsto_volume_restrict_totalLengthFilter_disjWithin_nhds_zero\"><span class=\"name\">AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval</span>.<span class=\"name\">tendsto_volume_restrict_totalLengthFilter_disjWithin_nhds_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a>\n  <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span>) =&gt;\n    <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace.volume\">MeasureTheory.volume</a>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Restrict.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.restrict\">restrict</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/UnorderedInterval.html#Set.uIoc\">Set.uIoc</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(⋃ <span class=\"fn\">i</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Range.html#Finset.range\">Finset.range</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.1</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/UnorderedInterval.html#Set.uIoc\">Set.uIoc</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.1</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.2</span></span>)</span></span>)</span>\n  <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.totalLengthFilter\">totalLengthFilter</a> ⊓ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.principal\">Filter.principal</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.disjWithin\">disjWithin</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>)</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.tendsto_volume_restrict_totalLengthFilter_disjWithin_nhds_zero","kind":"theorem","line":133,"name":"AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.tendsto_volume_restrict_totalLengthFilter_disjWithin_nhds_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.lean#L133-L145"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/AbsolutelyContinuous.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.tendsto_volume_totalLengthFilter_nhds_zero\"><span class=\"name\">AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval</span>.<span class=\"name\">tendsto_volume_totalLengthFilter_nhds_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a>\n  <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html